{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-jsx","path":"/projects/git-art/","result":{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/d438d/git-art.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 82%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/ba381/git-art.webp 200w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/7f61c/git-art.webp 400w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/d00b9/git-art.webp 800w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/92f8c/git-art.webp 1200w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/fad48/git-art.webp 1600w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/1f722/git-art.webp 2290w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/772e8/git-art.png 200w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/e17e5/git-art.png 400w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/5a190/git-art.png 800w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/c1b63/git-art.png 1200w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/29007/git-art.png 1600w,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/d438d/git-art.png 2290w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/5a190/git-art.png\"\n          alt=\"Git Art\"\n          title=\"Git Art\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>My roommate <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/timothylee0/\" title=\"Tim\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Tim</a> and I decided to start challenging ourselves with little applications we could develop.</p>\n<p>The first thing we thought of was a way to decorate your GitHub activity board, example below:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/d74fe/example-board.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 21.999999999999996%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/ba381/example-board.webp 200w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/7f61c/example-board.webp 400w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/d00b9/example-board.webp 800w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/4b3db/example-board.webp 1164w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/772e8/example-board.png 200w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/e17e5/example-board.png 400w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/5a190/example-board.png 800w,\n/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/d74fe/example-board.png 1164w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/95fe588730f42523bf7f534245c5a07b/5a190/example-board.png\"\n          alt=\"Example board\"\n          title=\"Example board\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The idea being that you could just draw or type (or both) anything that you wanted to on a canvas that represented your github activity board, and with one simple script you could create the required commits and upload that new repo to your GitHub.</p>\n<p>This is thanks to a feature/flaw in git that allows you to create commits (even empty commits) with any date attached.\nTherefore, all we need to do to generate a cute little activity graph is to simply work out the date ranges required, how many commits to make each day, and to generate a script that allows the user to do this.</p>\n<p>We used React for the front end, and wrote simple JavaScript functions to generate the bash script which is available for you to download and run.</p>\n<p>Made open source under the <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"http://www.wtfpl.net\" title=\"WTFPL licence\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">WTFPL licence</a>.</p>","excerpt":"My roommate  and I decided to start challenging ourselves with little applications we could develop. The first thing we thought of was a way to decorate your GitHub activity board, example below:  The…","frontmatter":{"title":"🖌 Git Art","date":"February, 2019","tech":["Javascript","React","Bash"],"link":"https://jamesjarvis.github.io/git-art/","source":"https://github.com/jamesjarvis/git-art","previewImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","width":1200,"height":983,"src":"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/f3583/git-art.png","srcSet":"/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/f3583/git-art.png 1x,\n/static/8f020bc41428522db3e5eb6a932a4ea9/bbee5/git-art.png 1.5x"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/projects/git-art/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/portfolio-site/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"🖥 Open Source Portfolio Website"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/projects/whatsupkent/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"📆 WhatsUpKent: Everything happening at the University of Kent"}}}}}